-- Gold Futures Decline 0.2%; Silver Futures Trade Little Changed
-- B y   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 2012-06-12T22:17:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/gold-futures-decline-0-2-silver-futures-trade-little-changed.html
Gold for August delivery in New York
declined 0.2 percent to $1,611.20 an ounce at 8:11 a.m. in
 Melbourne , while immediate-delivery bullion was little changed
at $1,610.22. Gold gained for the third straight session
yesterday on speculation that U.S. policy makers will announce
additional stimulus measures to boost growth.  Silver for July delivery was little changed at $28.925 an
ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Phoebe Sedgman in Melbourne at 
